                        <bindingDesc>
                             <binding contemporary="Ethiopian true">
                               <p>The manuscript is bound according to the traditional Ethiopian technique. The present binding is the first binding received by the manuscript.</p>
                                 <decoNote xml:id="b1" type="bindingMaterial">
                                   The book is bound in <material key="wood">wooden</material> boards.
                                 </decoNote>
                                 <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="Boards">
                                   The boards are flush with the bookblock and have shallow external bevels. The grain runs vertically.
                                   The external surface of the boards is polished and presents a finishing layer of dark colour. The inner surface and the edges are rough.
                                 </decoNote>
                                 <decoNote xml:id="b4" type="SewingStations">3</decoNote>
                                 <decoNote xml:id="b5">
                                   Chainstitch sewing on three sewing stations; Z-plied thread.
                                   The sewing is closed in the last quire, by knotting the ends of the thread to each other.
                                 </decoNote>
                                 <decoNote xml:id="b6" type="Spine">
                                   The small holes close to the head and tail of the quires are probably what remains of quire tackets.
                                 </decoNote>
                                 <decoNote xml:id="b7" type="SlipCase">
                                   The manuscript is provided with a leather one-piece single-walled slip case with the remnant of a hinging strap.
                                   The case is equipped with a main tapered flap extending from the back to the front panel to cover the opening of the book compartment.
                                   The fragment of a narrow leather hanging strap passes through two flaps extending from the bottom panel of the case.
                                 </decoNote>
                             </binding>
                         </bindingDesc>


